    content: `
      <div class="article-header">
        <h2>KB-7012: Understanding Hardware IDs (HID)</h2>
        <span class="last-updated">Published: Sept 28, 2011 | Version: 1.4</span>
      </div>
      <div class="article-body">
        <p>At ENGIMO, we believe in true ownership. To ensure that your software remains an asset tied to your hardware, we use a <strong>Hardware Identifier (HID)</strong> system.</p>
        <h4>How the HID is generated</h4>
        <p>When you launch an ENGIMO product for the first time, our engine scans your system for non-volatile components. This includes your motherboard's GUID and your primary CPU's thermal signature profile.</p>
        <div class="kb-code">SYSTEM_HID: ENG-8821-BC99-AF01</div>
        <h4>Does this track me?</h4>
        <p>No. The HID is a one-way cryptographic hash. We do not know what kind of computer you have; we only know that "License A" belongs to "Machine B".</p>
      </div>
                        `
  },
